📘 Subject: General Studies Paper I (Prelims – Polity)
🧠 Topic: Directive Principles of State Policy (DPSP)

(Very important for Prelims + extremely important for Mains.)

1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 What are Directive Principles?

Directive Principles are guidelines given to the government to establish:

Social justice

Economic welfare

Welfare state

📌 Mentioned in Part IV (Articles 36–51).

🔵 Key Features

Non-justiciable (cannot be enforced in court)

Fundamental in governance

Moral obligations on state

📌 Courts cannot enforce DPSPs but they are important for policy making.

🔹 Source

Inspired from Irish Constitution

🔴 Classification of DPSPs
1️⃣ Socialist Principles

Aim: Welfare state

Equal pay for equal work

Right to work

Protection of workers

Reduce inequality

2️⃣ Gandhian Principles

Based on Gandhi’s ideas:

Village panchayats

Cottage industries

Prohibition of alcohol

Protection of cows

3️⃣ Liberal-Intellectual Principles

Uniform Civil Code

Separation of judiciary and executive

Promotion of international peace

🔹 Important Articles
Article	Provision
38	Social order
39	Economic justice
40	Panchayati Raj
44	Uniform Civil Code
45	Free education
48A	Environment protection
🔹 DPSP vs Fundamental Rights
Feature	DPSP	Fundamental Rights
Nature	Non-justiciable	Justiciable
Focus	Welfare	Individual rights
Enforceable	No	Yes

📌 Both are complementary.

🔹 Importance

Helps in making laws

Promotes welfare state

Guides governance

Basis for policies (education, health, etc.)

